SIMPLE: suctorial
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Suctorial
<hw>Suc*to"ri*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>sugere</ets>, <ets>suctum</ets>, to suck.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Adapted for sucking; living by sucking; <as>as,
the humming birds are <ex>suctorial</ex> birds</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Capable of adhering by suction;
<as>as, the <ex>suctorial</ex> fishes</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Suctorian</ent>⟦br⟧
